Company Overview of Sterling Capital Management LLC



Snapshot People




Company Overview
The firm primarily provides its services to high net worth individuals. It also provides its services to public, sub-advisory, investment companies, pension and profit sharing plans, pooled investment vehicles, charitable organizations, corporations, state or municipal government entities, endowment, foundation, healthcare companies, WRAP programs, insurance, and Taft-Harley. The firm manages client-focused equity and fixed income portfolios. It launches and manages equity, fixed income, and balanced mutual funds for its clients. The firm invests in the public equity and fixed income markets of the United States. It typically makes its equity investments in value stocks of small-cap and mid-...
The firm primarily provides its services to high net worth individuals. It also provides its services to public, sub-advisory, investment companies, pension and profit sharing plans, pooled investment vehicles, charitable organizations, corporations, state or municipal government entities, endowment, foundation, healthcare companies, WRAP programs, insurance, and Taft-Harley. The firm manages client-focused equity and fixed income portfolios. It launches and manages equity, fixed income, and balanced mutual funds for its clients. The firm invests in the public equity and fixed income markets of the United States. It typically makes its equity investments in value stocks of small-cap and mid-cap companies. The firm employs a fundamental analysis with a bottom-up stock picking approach to create its equity portfolios. It benchmarks the performance of its small-cap portfolio against the Russell 2000 Value Index; small/mid cap portfolio against the Russell 2500 Value Index; and mid-cap portfolio against the Russell Mid Cap Value Index. The firm employs a value-oriented approach for short term fixed income portfolios. It was founded in 1970 and is based in Charlotte, North Carolina with additional offices in Atlanta, Georgia; Burlingame, California; Raleigh, North Carolina; Washington, District Of Columbia; and Virginia Beach, Virginia. Sterling Capital Management LLC operates as a subsidiary of BB&T Corporation.
Detailed Description


